question:
Company A with registered office in Shanghai has created a special and unique design on a fabric that they use in the production and sale of their goods. What sort of intellectual property right could they claim and for what period in time?
i. Company A can claim a copyright for the duration of 50 years since the goods on which the design is applied were first sold on the Chinese market;
ii. The PRC has not enacted laws that protect trademarks and/or designs.
iii. As Company A has not registered the design, it cannot claim any intellectual property rights on it;
iv. As Company A has not registered the design, it cannot claim any intellectual property rights;

In relation to the Closer Economic Partnership Agreement concluded between Hong Kong SAR and the PRC, which one of the following is correct:
i. Since the Closer Economic Partnership Agreement came into force, all foreign investment must be channelled through Hong Kong, meaning it is mandatory to first establish a holding company in Hong Kong.
ii. Together with the PRC’s Pearl River Delta Area it creates a common economic market similar to the European Union;
iii. It creates a form of free trade area in order to liberalize trade in goods, in services and investment facilitation between the PRC and Hong Kong SAR;
iv. It is an agreement on the mutual recognition and enforcement of civil and commercial cases;

In which one of the following cases is the termination of the employment contract not in violation of the Chinese Employment Contract Law?
i. The employer terminates the employment contract after expiry of the probationary period with 30 days' notice without cause;
ii. The employer terminates the employment contract during the probationary period with immediate effect and without cause, although the employee fulfils his duties.
iii. The employee terminates the employment contract after expiry of the probationary period with 30 days' notice without cause;
iv. The employee terminates the employment contract after expiry of the probationary period with immediate effect and without cause;

Why was the sale of iPads in China blocked in February 2012?
i. A local Chinese company was registered as the owner of the "iPad" trademark in the Chinese trademark register and demanded blocking on the basis of its trademark law;
ii. The sale of iPads was banned by the Ministry of Commerce (MOFCOM) because Apple had fixed the resale prices with the distributors, which is not permitted under Chinese competition law;
iii. As a result of Apple's circumvention of merger control, the Department of Commerce (MOFCOM) has banned the sale of iPads in China;
iv. The iPads do not comply with the local approval regulations of the Chinese Ministry of Communications.

Which statement is correct if the investment vehicle is an "equity joint venture"?
i. The passing of resolutions cannot be impaired by blocking minorities;
ii. There is no joint venture contract, which excludes a possible liability for a breach of contract by the other party;
iii. According to the legal provisions, all decisions must be taken unanimously by the parties;
iv. Equity joint ventures are forms of investment based on consensus.

Which one of the following is not regulated under the Closer Economic Partnership Arrangement concluded between the People's Republic of China and Hong Kong regulate?
i. Access to investment in the PRC for companies qualified under the CEPA at terms preferred compared to the WTO;
ii. Regulation of transport routes across the border between Mainland China (PRC) and the Hong Kong SAR;
iii. Liberalisation of trade in goods between Mainland China and Hong Kong;
iv. Liberalisation of trade in services between Mainland China (PRC) and Hong Kong;

China is trying to steer foreign investments into certain areas with various measures under the last and current five-year plans. Which of the following areas is not included?
i. Investments in the central and western parts of the country;
ii. High-tech, new and adapted technology;
iii. Projects that save energy and raw material.
iv. Focus of the foreign investment in Shanghai;

Which of the following statements applies in connection with a Hybrid Co-operative Joint Venture?
i. No local Chinese partner is required.
ii. Although a registered capital is provided for, the shareholders are also personally liable for the liabilities of the Hybrid Co-operative Joint Venture;
iii. It is not a form of investment based on consensus;
iv. The participation in the profits and liquidation proceeds of the Hybrid Co-operative Joint Venture is not necessarily based on the proportion of the participation in the registered capital;

Regarding the establishment of Foreign Invested Enterprises in 2016 the PRC introduced a new system, so-called “registration for the records”. Which change resulted from this amendment?
i. All foreign invested companies (FIE) only need to register, but no longer require approval from the Ministry of Commerce;
ii. Since autumn 2016, the approval of the Ministry of Commerce has been required for all foreign invested companies (FIE);
iii. Those foreign invested enterprises (FIE) whose business activities are not on the negative list only have to register but no longer require a permit from the Ministry of Commerce;
iv. The negative list authorizes the local authorities to subject the establishment of foreign invested companies to the approval of the Ministry of Commerce on a case-by-case basis.

In relation to the Wholly Foreign-owned Enterprise (WFOE) which one of the following statements is correct:
i. Its registered capital is held by investors with registered office outside of the PRC.
ii. The entire registered capital must be held by one single investor;
iii. It may not be used for investment in the PRC by a company with registered office in the Hong Kong SAR;
iv. It is the only available investment vehicle in the PRC’s central and Western regions;

What are so-called "variable equity interest structures" used for by foreign investors?
i. Special contractual agreements and structuring of investments that enable foreign investors to gain control over companies in industrial sectors in which foreign control is not permitted;
ii. Special provisions in the articles of association of an Equity Joint Venture which permit an ongoing adjustment of the amount of interest (variable interest) on the parties’ participation in the registered capital;
iii. The flexible duration of a Foreign Investment Enterprise, which allows the parties to agree on a specific duration of their company.
iv. Special provisions in the articles of association of an Equity Joint Venture that allow the PRC government to increase / decrease its participations in Equity Joint Ventures with foreign investors;

Which of the following statements applies in the bilateral relationship between Switzerland and Hong Kong?
i. Switzerland and Hong Kong have concluded an agreement on the enforcement and recognition of judgments;
ii. Switzerland and Hong Kong have concluded a free trade agreement;
iii. Switzerland and China have not concluded a bilateral agreement, as Hong Kong is not entitled to enter into bilateral agreements with countries.
iv. Switzerland and Hong Kong have not concluded a double taxation agreement;

Regarding the One Belt One Road Initiative which one is the correct statement?
i. The initiative has been introduced in order to include Hong Kong into the Pearl River Delta Initiative;
ii. The initiative has been introduced by the PRC in order to remain a player in the negotiations with North Korea to create a nuclear-free North Korea;
iii. The initiative has been introduced in order to reduce the tax rates in the countries along the Old Silk Road;
iv. The initiative has been introduced in order to bring together China’s goals in order to establish an intercontinental infrastructure network between Europe, Africa, Asia and China.

What does the bifurcated legal system mean in connection with Chinese investment law?
i. The term refers to the opinion of investors that enforcement in China may be more difficult for foreign companies as compared to local companies;
ii. For foreign investments, additional laws and regulations must be observed in comparison to local Chinese investors which do not apply to local Chinese investors;
iii. Compared to foreign investors who directly hold a subsidiary in China, other legal provisions apply to investors who use a holding company based in Hong Kong for their investment;
iv. Other legal provisions apply to investors domiciled abroad and investors domiciled in Hong Kong;

Regarding Hong Kong and the term “one country two systems” which one of the following is correct?
i. Hong Kong has integrated its economic system with the PRC and does not maintain its own currency;
ii. The custom’s system of Hong Kong has been integrated into the PRC and Hong Kong does no longer maintain own borders with own customs;
iii. The highest instance for court cases in Hong Kong is the PRC Supreme People’s Court;
iv. Hong Kong has its own legal system, meaning that the laws of the PRC do not apply in Hong Kong.

What is the meaning of "rule by law" versus "rule of law"?
i. A "rule by law" system uses law as an instrument of the state, a "rule of law" system corresponds to a constitutional system according to Western understanding.
ii. The PRC has not passed any laws;
iii. In the PRC, the laws are passed directly by the Communist Party;
iv. A "rule by law" system uses law as an instrument of the state, a "rule of law" system corresponds to a constitutional system according to Western understanding.

What major amendment was made by the revision of the Chinese Trademark Law in 2014?
i. Trademarks may now also be registered in Chinese characteristics;
ii. Against the background of the creation of famous Chinese trademarks, the priority right of famous foreign trademarks is limited.
iii. Trademarks applied for registration by foreigners take precedence over local applicants;
iv. The strict "first-to-file system" has been weakened to the effect that the registration and use of a trademark must follow the principle of good faith, otherwise no priority right can be asserted;

Which one of the following was the main goal of China’s Open Door Policy that was introduced in 1978
i. To adopt a Western-type legal System;
ii. To bring foreign investment to China and to obtain advance and adequate technology and generate foreign exchange through trade;
iii. To attract foreigners from Western countries to work in China.
iv. To open-up China for investment by Private Equity;
